Changed `content/papers/ghost.modes.md` with minimal structural QA edits only.

Summary of changes:
- Added KaTeX equation tags to make referenced equations visibly numbered and discoverable:
  - `\tag{1}` on the TM\(_{01}\) field expression
  - `\tag{2}` on the interface-matching condition
  - `\tag{3}` on the \(\omega^2\) approximation
  - `\tag{4}` on the \(x_0\) expression
  - `\tag{5}` on the \(Q\) estimate
  - `\tag{6}`, `\tag{7}` on the two crude-estimate equations
  - `\tag{8}` on \(\alpha\)
  - `\tag{9}`, `\tag{10}` on the \(\delta V\) inequalities
- Inserted one missing blank line before `# Periodic Structures` to enforce paragraph/section boundary readability.
- Removed one trailing whitespace character.

Self-check:
- Paragraph/section boundaries are blank-line separated where intended.
- In-text equation references `(1), (2), (3), (4), (6), (7), (10)` now map to visible display-equation numbers.
- No paper meaning/content or math expressions were changed beyond numbering markup.
